    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ 395\u00b0F/ Gas 6</p><p>Peel and finely chop 1/4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1/2]</span> <strong>red onion</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mauritian-fish-vindaye-with-buttery-bread/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> and <strong>tomato </strong>to a bowl with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> tomato & onion salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mauritian-fish-vindaye-with-buttery-bread/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and<strong> remaining red onion</strong> into wedges, then separate the wedges into petals</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion petals </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to brown and soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mauritian-fish-vindaye-with-buttery-bread/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the onion is cooking, chop the <strong>green chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half, deseed, and slice finely</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ground turmeric</strong>,<strong> fenugreek</strong>, <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> and <strong>black mustard seeds</strong> to a bowl</p><p>Add 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]<strong> </span>vegetable oil</strong>, 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]<strong> </span>cold water</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>spice paste</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mauritian-fish-vindaye-with-buttery-bread/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>basa fillets </strong>into large, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mauritian-fish-vindaye-with-buttery-bread/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion petals have softened, add the <strong>chopped basa</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown slightly</p><p>Add the <strong>cider vinegar</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until evaporated</p><p>Add the<strong> spice paste</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until the fish is cooked through and everything's fragrant \u2013 this is your <strong>fish vindaye</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mauritian-fish-vindaye-with-buttery-bread/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>ciabatta rolls </strong>to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 3-4 min or until warm and crusty</p><p>Once done, carefully cut the <strong>warmed ciabatta</strong> in half and spread each half with<strong> butter</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mauritian-fish-vindaye-with-buttery-bread/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> fish vindaye</strong> with the<strong> tomato & onion salad </strong>and <strong>buttery bread</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
